In developed nations, the lifetime risk of a woman dying as a result of one of her pregnancies is around 1 in 2800, but in places like sub-Saharan Africa, about 1 out of every 16 women will die as a result of one of her pregnancies over the course of her childbearing years"> The number of induced abortions declined worldwide between 1995 and 2003, from nearly 46 million to approximately 42 million.
